                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1va">Fols. 1va-4</locus>vb, 105vab: Mälkǝʾa śǝllase “Image of the Trinity” (ChRep 191, no. 20). <q xml:lang="gez">Fols. 1va: ሰላም፡ ለህላዌክሙ፡ ዘይመውዕ፡ ህላዌያት። ለረኪበ፡ ስሙ፡ ኅቡዕ፡ አመ፡ ወጠንኩ፡ ተምኔተ። እምግብርክሙ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ሶበ፡ ረከብኩ፡ አስማተ፨…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in a fine hand, possibly the same hand which inserted some of the names in the supplication formulas.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#105ra">Fol. 105ra</locus>b: Transaction note.<q xml:lang="gez"> Fol. 105rab: ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘኃለቃ፡ ገብረ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አርአያ፡ ዖምጽጌ፡ ዘሴጦ፡ በ፵፬ብር፡ መድኅኑ፡ አቶ፡ ወልደ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ካህሳይ፡ … በዘመነ፡ ማርቆስ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡ በመስፍንነ፡ ራስ፡ ጉግሣ፡ በጳጳስነ፡ ማቴዎስ፡ ፲፱፻፳፪ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ ፲፯ቀን፡ ሰኔ፡ ተገዛ፡ ዘሰረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ በስልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ ለይኩን። ።</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note is partly erased, written in Amharic.
The Ms. was sold by haläqa Gäbrä Ǝgziʾabḥer for 44 Bǝrr to ʾato Wäldä Mikaʾel Kahsay, on 17 Säne 1922 year of mercy (= 24 June, 1930 A.D.) in the time of ras Gugsa (d. March 1930?) and Metropolitan Matewos (d. December 1926).
Many names of witnesses are also mentioned.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#106vb">Fol. 106vb</locus>: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 106vb: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘወይዘሮ፡ ብሪቱ፡ ዘተሣያጠቶ፡ በ፶፡ ብር፡ ወወሀበታ፡ ለማርያም፡ መይ፡ አብአ፡ ከመ፡ ይኩና፡ መርሐ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ኦአበውየ፡ ኢትርስዑኒ፡ አቡነ፡ ዘበሰማያት፡</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note states that Wälättä Bǝrritu bought the Ms. for 50 Bǝrr and donated it to the church of ʾAbʾa.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Scribbles in the margins: fols. 5r, 56v, 57r, 90r, 95r, 103v.&#xD;
- The names of Wälättä Maryam and Gäbrä Krǝstos are written in the supplication formulas, in modern pen: fols. 76v, 78rb.</item>
